description.plain:
“I’ll Go Running” is the second single and the opening track off Planet (i), Squirrel Flower’s 2021 album. The subtle build of the track sees her declaring an intention to be “newer than before.”

Said Ella Williams of the song for Rolling Stone:

“’I’ll Go Running’ is about the darker side of being an artist — the pressure to make things brand new, shocking, to give everything away and open yourself completely without always getting intentional listening and consumption in return. To be vulnerable to a knife. To be fresh, new, to give it all away. But it’s powerful to offer yourself and your art without fear, which is what I try to do with this album. That’s why this is the opening track.”

description.plain: In a statement, Williams explained that she wrote the lyrics in character: “‘Hurt a Fly’ is me embodying a persona of gaslighting, narcissistic soft-boy type shit. I wanted to see what it was like to be a character trying to skirt around accountability. It’s an angry and unhinged song.”
